05/11/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivica Racan was released Tuesday (4 November) from the Magdalena Cardiac Hospital in Krapinske Toplice, northwest of Zagreb, after a thorough medical exam due to cardiac problems, according to representatives of the ruling Social Democratic Party (SDP). The government confirmed the news, saying Racan experienced exhaustion over the past few days. Later Tuesday, Racan appeared during a presentation of the SDP's election platform and said he was feeling well. (HINA, BBC, MediaScan - 04/11/03)
